Flask Web Page with Python Login Module
A simple yet secure web application built using Flask, featuring a login module that handles user authentication. This project demonstrates how to implement user login functionality in Flask with a clean, organized codebase.

Features
User Authentication: Allows users to register, log in, and log out securely.
Session Management: Maintains user sessions using Flask's built-in session management, ensuring persistent user state.
Password Hashing: Implements password hashing for secure credential storage.
Responsive Design: Web page layout optimized for both desktop and mobile devices.
Easy Setup and Configuration: Simple steps to get the app running on your local machine.
Technologies Used
Flask: Web framework for Python
SQLite: Lightweight database for user data storage
HTML, CSS: Front-end for the web page
Jinja2: Template engine for Flask
Getting Started
To run this project locally, follow these steps:

Prerequisites
Python 3.x installed on your system.
Basic knowledge of Flask and Python.
